cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SY 

The paper deals with subspace segmentation and has applications in computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also presents a new algorithm for subspace segmentation, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The paper uses polynomial representations and PCA, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and control problems, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely but still possible category.
